Step 1: Identify Debt and Assets values at the end of the reporting period.  
 • Total Liabilities (Debt) is typically the sum of Accounts Payable and Taxes Payable.  
  – Accounts Payable = 1,000,000.00  
  – Taxes Payable = 903,121.89  
  – Total Liabilities = 1,000,000.00 + 903,121.89 = 1,903,121.89  

Step 2: Identify Total Assets at the end of the reporting period.  
 • Total Assets = 31,154,033.87  

Step 3: Compute the Debt to Asset Ratio.  
 • Debt to Asset Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Assets  
 • Ratio = 1,903,121.89 / 31,154,033.87 ≈ 0.0611  

Step 4: Rounding the result to two decimals (if applicable), the ratio becomes approximately 0.06.

Thus, the solution is:
{
  "solution": {
    "Debt to Asset Ratio": "0.06"
  }
}
